In this article, President Trump expresses his support for the military and emphasizes the importance of funding it. He states that if the country shuts down, the budget should be handled differently, particularly in terms of prioritizing the military. Trump mentions that the military has been depleted over the years and that he is working towards rebuilding it to make it the best in the world. He also highlights the positive impact of tax cuts and tax reform on job creation. Trump warns that if there is a government shutdown, the military would be the group that loses the most, and he vows to always support and fund the military. The article ends with Trump stating that it is up to the Democrats whether or not there will be a government shutdown.